description: A Boeing top official told Congress that employees looked extensively for documents on the door plug and it's likely that such paperwork never existed.
title: Boeing says it can't find documents on the door plug that blew off mid-air

description: Batool Cakes, a professional bakery in Rafah, has reopened to meet the demand of displaced Palestinians seeking cakes to celebrate life even amid war.
title: Cake in the time of war, in Gaza

description: Three National Guard soldiers and a Border Patrol agent were on board when a helicopter crashed near the Mexican border. A soldier was seriously injured.
title: 2 National Guard members and Border Patrol agent are killed in Texas helicopter crash

description: International Women's Day, on March 8, celebrates the achievements of women. We share stories from women in the the Kibera community, which locals call a "slum," about their setbacks and successes.
title: Resilient and strong: Voices of women from Kenya's largest 'slum'

description: A glimpse at the world of women bullfighters in Mexico City, as the spectacle makes its return two years after a judge banned it — generating excitement from fans and criticism over animal cruelty.
title: Mexico's female matadors return to the world's largest bullring

description: The state of Israeli society, five months after the Oct. 7 attack, is crucial to understanding where the Israel-Hamas conflict might lead. Here are five ways Israel has been transformed.
title: Five ways Israelis have changed, after 5 months of war

description: Former President Donald Trump's vice presidential pick will say a lot about how he sees the future of the Republican Party and how much he values loyalty.
title: Now that he's the presumptive nominee, Trump readies next campaign: who will be VP?

description: There would be no film without film editing. And yet, its practitioners don't often grace the cover of magazines.
title: The pioneering women behind the invisible art of film editing

description: An attack by Houthi rebels set off explosions ahead of a Singapore-flagged vessel in the Gulf of Aden, the latest in a campaign of assaults by the Iranian-backed group over Israel's war on Hamas.
title: Yemen's rebels target Singapore-flagged ship as U.S. and allies down Houthi drones

description: Led by Texas, the states who brought the lawsuit against the Biden administration argued the program is forcing them to spend millions on health care, education and public safety for the migrants.
title: Judge upholds program allowing 30,000 migrants from 4 countries into the US per month

description: Senators voted 75 to 22 to approve a package of six spending bills that will last until the end of the fiscal year on September 30.
title: Senate passes spending package hours ahead of shutdown deadline

description: In last night's State of The Union, the murder of 22-year-old Laken Riley took center stage. The suspect is a migrant. Republicans say immigration leads to crime, but there's no evidence of that.
title: Immigrants are less likely to commit crimes than U.S.-born Americans, studies find
